<%# JSON-LD schemas %>
<%= breadcrumb_schema([
  { name: "Home", url: root_url },
  { name: "Suites", url: nil },
  { name: "Fitness Suite" }
]) %>

<%= faq_schema([
  { question: "What is a fitness calculator suite?", answer: "A fitness calculator suite is a guided workflow that walks you through the key health and nutrition calculations in the right order. Starting with BMI, then TDEE, macros, and calorie planning, each step builds on the previous one to create a complete fitness plan." },
  { question: "Should I calculate BMI or TDEE first?", answer: "Start with BMI to understand your current body composition relative to your height, then move to TDEE to determine how many calories you burn daily. Your TDEE depends on your activity level and body metrics, so knowing where you stand with BMI provides useful context." },
  { question: "How do macros relate to TDEE?", answer: "Your TDEE (Total Daily Energy Expenditure) tells you how many total calories you need per day. Macros break those calories down into protein, carbohydrates, and fat based on your fitness goals -- whether you want to lose fat, build muscle, or maintain your current weight." },
  { question: "What is a calorie deficit and when should I use one?", answer: "A calorie deficit means eating fewer calories than your TDEE so your body uses stored energy (fat) for fuel. A moderate deficit of 300-500 calories per day is generally recommended for sustainable weight loss of about 0.5-1 pound per week." }
]) %>

<%# Breadcrumbs %>
<%= render "shared/breadcrumbs", items: [
  { name: "Home", url: root_path },
  { name: "Suites" },
  { name: "Fitness Suite" }
] %>

<div class="mb-10">
  <h1 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-extrabold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mb-4">Fitness Calculator Suite</h1>
  <p class="text-lg text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 max-w-3xl">Build a complete fitness and nutrition plan step by step. Start with your body metrics, calculate your energy needs, then dial in your macros and calorie targets.</p>
</div>

<%= render "shared/ad_slot", slot: "leaderboard" %>

<div class="mt-8 space-y-6" data-controller="suite-stepper">
  <%# Step 1: BMI %>
  <div class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-900 rounded-2xl border border-gray-200/80 dark:border-gray-800 overflow-hidden">
    <button data-action="click->suite-stepper#toggle" class="w-full flex items-center justify-between p-6 text-left group">
      <div class="flex items-center gap-4">
        <div class="w-10 h-10 bg-gradient-to-br from-green-500 to-emerald-600 rounded-xl flex items-center justify-center text-white font-bold text-lg">1</div>
        <div>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 dark:text-white group-hover:text-green-600 dark:group-hover:text-green-400 transition-colors">Check Your BMI</h2>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400 mt-1">Understand where you stand with your body mass index</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-gray-400 transition-transform" data-suite-stepper-target="chevron" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"/></svg>
    </button>
    <div data-suite-stepper-target="panel" class="border-t border-gray-200/80 dark:border-gray-800 p-6">
      <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 mb-4">Start by calculating your BMI to get a baseline understanding of your current body composition relative to your height and weight.</p>
      <%= link_to "Open BMI Calculator", health_bmi_path, class: "inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-5 py-2.5 bg-gradient-to-r from-green-600 to-emerald-600 text-white rounded-xl hover:from-green-700 hover:to-emerald-700 transition-all text-sm font-medium", data: { turbo_frame: "_top" } %>
    </div>
  </div>

  <%# Step 2: TDEE %>
  <div class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-900 rounded-2xl border border-gray-200/80 dark:border-gray-800 overflow-hidden">
    <button data-action="click->suite-stepper#toggle" class="w-full flex items-center justify-between p-6 text-left group">
      <div class="flex items-center gap-4">
        <div class="w-10 h-10 bg-gradient-to-br from-green-500 to-emerald-600 rounded-xl flex items-center justify-center text-white font-bold text-lg">2</div>
        <div>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 dark:text-white group-hover:text-green-600 dark:group-hover:text-green-400 transition-colors">Calculate Your TDEE</h2>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400 mt-1">Find out how many calories you burn each day</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-gray-400 transition-transform" data-suite-stepper-target="chevron" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"/></svg>
    </button>
    <div data-suite-stepper-target="panel" class="hidden border-t border-gray-200/80 dark:border-gray-800 p-6">
      <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 mb-4">Your Total Daily Energy Expenditure (TDEE) is the total number of calories you burn per day including exercise. This is the foundation for any diet plan.</p>
      <%= link_to "Open TDEE Calculator", health_tdee_path, class: "inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-5 py-2.5 bg-gradient-to-r from-green-600 to-emerald-600 text-white rounded-xl hover:from-green-700 hover:to-emerald-700 transition-all text-sm font-medium", data: { turbo_frame: "_top" } %>
    </div>
  </div>

  <%# Step 3: Macros %>
  <div class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-900 rounded-2xl border border-gray-200/80 dark:border-gray-800 overflow-hidden">
    <button data-action="click->suite-stepper#toggle" class="w-full flex items-center justify-between p-6 text-left group">
      <div class="flex items-center gap-4">
        <div class="w-10 h-10 bg-gradient-to-br from-green-500 to-emerald-600 rounded-xl flex items-center justify-center text-white font-bold text-lg">3</div>
        <div>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 dark:text-white group-hover:text-green-600 dark:group-hover:text-green-400 transition-colors">Plan Your Macros</h2>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400 mt-1">Break down your calories into protein, carbs, and fat</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-gray-400 transition-transform" data-suite-stepper-target="chevron" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"/></svg>
    </button>
    <div data-suite-stepper-target="panel" class="hidden border-t border-gray-200/80 dark:border-gray-800 p-6">
      <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 mb-4">Use your TDEE from Step 2 to calculate the ideal split of protein, carbohydrates, and fat for your fitness goals.</p>
      <%= link_to "Open Macro Calculator", health_macro_path, class: "inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-5 py-2.5 bg-gradient-to-r from-green-600 to-emerald-600 text-white rounded-xl hover:from-green-700 hover:to-emerald-700 transition-all text-sm font-medium", data: { turbo_frame: "_top" } %>
    </div>
  </div>

  <%# Step 4: Calorie Deficit %>
  <div class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-900 rounded-2xl border border-gray-200/80 dark:border-gray-800 overflow-hidden">
    <button data-action="click->suite-stepper#toggle" class="w-full flex items-center justify-between p-6 text-left group">
      <div class="flex items-center gap-4">
        <div class="w-10 h-10 bg-gradient-to-br from-green-500 to-emerald-600 rounded-xl flex items-center justify-center text-white font-bold text-lg">4</div>
        <div>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 dark:text-white group-hover:text-green-600 dark:group-hover:text-green-400 transition-colors">Set Your Calorie Target</h2>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400 mt-1">Calculate the right calorie deficit for sustainable weight loss</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-gray-400 transition-transform" data-suite-stepper-target="chevron" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"/></svg>
    </button>
    <div data-suite-stepper-target="panel" class="hidden border-t border-gray-200/80 dark:border-gray-800 p-6">
      <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 mb-4">If your goal is weight loss, use your TDEE to calculate a safe calorie deficit that promotes fat loss while preserving muscle mass.</p>
      <%= link_to "Open Calorie Deficit Calculator", health_calorie_deficit_path, class: "inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-5 py-2.5 bg-gradient-to-r from-green-600 to-emerald-600 text-white rounded-xl hover:from-green-700 hover:to-emerald-700 transition-all text-sm font-medium", data: { turbo_frame: "_top" } %>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<%= render "shared/ad_slot", slot: "in_content" %>

<article class="prose prose-lg dark:prose-invert max-w-none mt-12">
  <h2>How to Use the Fitness Calculator Suite</h2>
  <p>Whether you want to lose weight, build muscle, or simply eat healthier, this calculator suite takes you through the process in the right order. Each step produces numbers you will use in the next step.</p>

  <h3>Step-by-Step Guide</h3>
  <ol>
    <li><strong>Check your BMI</strong> -- Get a baseline snapshot of where you are today relative to healthy weight ranges.</li>
    <li><strong>Calculate TDEE</strong> -- Determine how many calories your body burns each day including your activity level.</li>
    <li><strong>Plan macros</strong> -- Break your daily calories into the right balance of protein, carbs, and fat for your goals.</li>
    <li><strong>Set calorie target</strong> -- If you want to lose weight, calculate how much to eat below your TDEE for safe, sustainable progress.</li>
  </ol>

  <h3>Why Order Matters</h3>
  <p>Many people jump straight to calorie counting without understanding their baseline energy needs. By starting with BMI and TDEE, you build a foundation of knowledge about your body. Your macro split is meaningless without knowing your total calorie target, and your calorie target is meaningless without knowing your TDEE. This suite ensures you never skip a critical step.</p>

  <h3>Customizing for Your Goals</h3>
  <p>If your goal is muscle building rather than weight loss, you can skip Step 4 (Calorie Deficit) and instead add a moderate surplus of 200-300 calories above your TDEE. The macro calculator in Step 3 will help you emphasize protein intake, which is essential for muscle growth regardless of whether you are in a surplus or deficit.</p>
</article>

<%= render "shared/ad_slot", slot: "multiplex" %>
